@prefix : <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix onto: <../../ontology.ttl#> .

<> a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "Model Identity Resolution Gate"@en ;
    schema:description "Blocking gate: resolve the active LLM model identity from three chained sources. No file write, artifact routing decision, or whoami response may proceed with 'unresolved' model identity."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-07-14T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:dateModified "2026-07-14T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:author <https://linkedin.com/in/kidehen#this> ;
    schema:about :step-modelIdentityResolution ;
    schema:step :step-resolutionSourceChain, :step-resolutionEnvVarFallback,
        :step-resolutionElicitUser, :step-resolutionProhibitedDefaults ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <../preferences.ttl>, <artifact-routing.ttl> .

# ── Step 1: Three-Source Resolution Chain ────────────────────────────────────

:step-resolutionSourceChain a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position "1"^^xsd:integer ;
    schema:name "Resolve model identity from three sources in strict priority order"@en ;
    schema:text """The agent MUST resolve its active model identity from these three sources, in strict priority:

SOURCE 1 — System Prompt (highest priority):
  Read the system prompt for explicit model identification phrases:
    "You are powered by the model {name}"
    "You are {name}"
    "Model: {name}"
    "{provider} {model-name}"
  If the prompt names a model, use it as the canonical model identity.

SOURCE 2 — Environment Variables (fallback when Source 1 is silent or ambiguous):
  When the system prompt says only generic text like "You are an expert coding assistant
  operating inside {harness-name}" without naming a model, check these env vars:
    ANTHROPIC_MODEL      (e.g., claude-deepseek-v4-pro[1m])
    ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL   (e.g., https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic → DeepSeek backend)
    OPENAI_MODEL         (e.g., gpt-5)
    GOOGLE_MODEL         (e.g., gemini-2.5-pro)
    MODEL                (generic fallback)
  Parse the value to extract the canonical model name and family. If ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL
  points to a different provider (e.g., api.deepseek.com), the MODEL env var value
  determines the model family, but note the routing in session context.

SOURCE 3 — Elicit from User (last resort):
  If both Source 1 and Source 2 fail to yield a model identity, ask the user:
    "I cannot determine which LLM model I am. Which model is powering this session?"
  Do not proceed with any file write or whoami response until the user answers.

This chain mirrors the WebID-TLS verification pattern (local first, remote fallback)
and the credentials-root resolution gate (search, then elicit — never guess).
All three sources are inexpensive to check (prompt text, env vars, one user question),
so there is no legitimate reason to skip the chain and return 'unresolved'."""@en .

# ── Step 2: Map Resolved Identity to Output Root ─────────────────────────────

:step-resolutionEnvVarFallback a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position "2"^^xsd:integer ;
    schema:name "Map the resolved model identity to its canonical output root via core.ttl"@en ;
    schema:text """Once the model identity is resolved, map it to its output path:

1. Match the model family to a core.ttl output path entity:
     DeepSeek V4 Pro / claude-deepseek-v4-pro → :deepseekOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/DeepSeek/
     Claude Sonnet / Opus → :claudeOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/Claude Generated/
     GPT-5 Chat → (see step-gpt5ChatCodexOutputDirs) → {LLM_ROOT}/GPT5-Chat-Generated/
     Grok → :grokOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/Grok/
     GLM → :glmOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/glm/
     Big Pickle → :bigPickleOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/Big Pickle/
     kimi → :kimiOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/kimi/
     MiniMax → :minimaxOutputPath → {LLM_ROOT}/MiniMax Generated/

2. If no matching core.ttl entry exists, elicit from the user where artifacts should
   be routed — never default to a random model's directory.

3. Confirm the resolved root internally. All subsequent writes in the session use
   this root without re-derivation.

This step feeds both artifact routing (:step-outputDirs) and whoami responses
(:step-whoamiFormat)."""@en ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <../core.ttl>, <artifact-routing.ttl> .

# ── Step 3: Elicit When Unmappable ───────────────────────────────────────────

:step-resolutionElicitUser a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position "3"^^xsd:integer ;
    schema:name "Elicit from user when the resolved model identity has no core.ttl mapping"@en ;
    schema:text """EDGE CASE: a model identity is resolved (Source 1 or Source 2 succeeds) but
has no matching output path in core.ttl. Prompt the user:

  "I've identified my model as {model-name}, but there is no output path defined for
  it in core.ttl. Where should I route generated artifacts? Options: (1) add a new
  entry to core.ttl, (2) reuse an existing model's path, (3) specify a custom path."

Wait for the user's response before writing any files.

This gate exists because new LLMs are added regularly, and defaulting to a
wrong model's directory (the 2026-06-09 World Cup meshup bug) or writing to
kg-output/ (the 2026-06-24 bug) are both worse than a 30-second elicitation."""@en .

# ── Step 4: Prohibited Defaults ──────────────────────────────────────────────

:step-resolutionProhibitedDefaults a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position "4"^^xsd:integer ;
    schema:name "Prohibited model identity defaults — never guess, never leave unresolved"@en ;
    schema:text """EXPLICITLY PROHIBITED when model identity cannot be resolved:
  • "model identity not specified in runtime" (leave unresolved)
  • Guessing from session file context
  • Guessing from conversation history
  • Guessing from working directory path
  • Defaulting to Claude Generated/ or any other model's directory
  • Using kg-output/, /tmp, or the repo root as a fallback destination

Every one of these is worse than a 30-second user elicitation. The model identity
resolution chain (Sources 1–3) is the only valid path — if all three fail, stop
and ask. An agent that cannot identify itself cannot responsibly route artifacts
or respond to whoami."""@en .
